assertAddOnAmount

java.lang.Object assertAddOnAmount(java.lang.Object request, java.lang.Object response, java.lang.Object addOnToAssert, java.lang.Object dbData)
This is used to validate if the AddOnAmount from the response matches the data stored in the database.
Returns:
Status of validation as a string. Following are the possible return statuses:
  • Matches. RequestData matches DB Data.
  • Mismatch. RequestData does not match DB Data.
  • Error. Request Data is empty.
  • Error. DB Data is empty.
  • Error. Request Data and DB Data is missing.
Parameters:
request - Soap request as a string.
response - Soap response as a string.
addOnToAssert - AddOn whose amount value needs to be validated.
dbData - AddOn Amount data from a prior executed SQL query as a string.
